There are days where I cry out of frustration because of the pressure and things being overwhelming, there are days where I don't get any sleep because I am up brainstorming all night, there are days where I am sick because of my Lyme disease, there are days where I have anxiety attacks because I suffer with severe anxiety but I do NOT give up. Keep going, pray, keep faith in God and just know it will work out trust me. I'm not where I want to be yet but I am still getting up everyday pushing. Sitting at home being upset and frustrated because you aren't where you want to be won't get you anywhere. You have to use your frustration as motivation, go harder for what you want. Even on the days you don't want to or feel like you can't, just get up and keep going. You never know how close you are and you never know who's watching. I promise y'all, if you stay consistent and never give up, you will make it. Careers just don't fall out the sky, you have to work hard! GO GET IT. I've been told no so many times, I've been left on read so many times but I did not give up. And again, I am not where I want to be yet but everyday I am one step closer.
